<h2>Ember2.0 - Data Down Actions Up; Stability without stagnation</h2>
<h3>Overview</h3>
<p>Emberjs is a fascinating javascript framework for a variety of reasons.  While they're far from perfect,
  all things considered are undeniably a rock solid choice to build your application on.  The areas they fall-short
  are currently under renovation and in the scheme of things can be viewed as short term inconveniences.

Emberjs is on their game in a very strong way.  They pioneered the industry leading router and shamelessly
cherry-picked the best characteristics of other frameworks.  “we don't claim to have a monopoly on good ideas” - Tom Dale

Considering we're talking about open-source software that by nature allows for such behavior it's hard to hate
(unless you're a disgruntled competitor who just watched their main advantage dissapear in a few short months cough cough*  react>.

Origin: Ember was founded in 2011 by Yaheuda Katz and is currently co-authored by Tom Dale.

Influence:  Admittedly, ember received a healthy influence by the popular <a href='http://rubyonrails.org/'>Ruby on Rails Project.</a>
And Yaheduas time spent working on the sproutcore team.</p>

